cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a novel technique for natural language processing, specifically for improving the output of Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR) systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses bidirectional recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper's approach could be extended to other sequence labeling tasks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision).
